jack2-pistomp (1.9.22-3) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Shrink JACK shm segment: build with --clients=64
    --ports-per-application=512 (36MB fixed base -> 8MB).
  * Ship jackdrc and jack.service so JACK startup changes reach devices over
    OTA. jackdrc moves to /usr/lib/pistomp/jackdrc so it is not a conffile;
    postinst renames any pre-existing /etc/jackdrc to /etc/jackdrc.obsolete
    with a header explaining the move.
  * jackdrc passes --port-max, derived from the board model (512 on Pi 5, else
    256) and overridable via JACK_PORT_MAX in /etc/default/jack. Upstream's
    2048-port default cost 102MB of mlocked shm; a pedalboard uses ~42 ports.

 -- pi-gen-pistomp <noreply@github.com>  Fri, 10 Jul 2026 03:31:46 +0000

jack2-pistomp (1.9.22-2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Conflicts/Replaces/versioned-Provides libjack-jackd2-0 so Debian's stock
    libjackserver.so.0 is never installed alongside this build.
  * Install libraries to the arm64 multiarch dir (/usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu)
    so the patched libjackserver wins in ld.so.cache. Previously the package
    installed to /usr/lib (not on the linker search path); jackd loaded the
    stock Debian libjackserver instead of the patched one, causing
    jack.service to crash-loop and mod-host to hang at boot.

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

